<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="28" type="notes on taxonomy">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="28">Notes on taxonomy.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="28">
<bibRefCitation pageId="5" pageNumber="28">Strohmeyer (1928)</bibRefCitation>
had placed this species as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Cypholoba" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cypholoba opulenta" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="opulenta">Cypholoba opulenta</taxonomicName>
but as pointed out by 
<bibRefCitation author="Basilewsky, P" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" pagination="107 - 111" title="Descriptions de Coleopteres Carabiques nouveaux d'Afrique et notes diverses sur des especes deja connues, III." volume="53" year="1948">Basilewsky (1948)</bibRefCitation>
this is clearly an error as the two species are quite distinct and have different proportions, vestiture, and surface sculpture.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
